WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.218 --> 00:00:03.551
(gentle galactic music)

00:00:11.420 --> 00:00:13.730
- So sometimes we get the question,

00:00:13.730 --> 00:00:17.230
why are there so many
negative reviews on X3?

00:00:17.230 --> 00:00:20.330
Now, the answer is, there aren't.

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:23.260
At first we were a little
confused by that question.

00:00:23.260 --> 00:00:24.540
I think what people mean is

00:00:24.540 --> 00:00:27.150
why are there negative comments?

00:00:27.150 --> 00:00:28.760
Like, there are certain websites

00:00:28.760 --> 00:00:31.060
that are kinda bodybuilding-focused

00:00:31.060 --> 00:00:34.110
that have a lot of comments,

00:00:34.110 --> 00:00:36.140
like "X3 doesn't work,"

00:00:36.140 --> 00:00:38.423
or "It's a scam," or whatever.

00:00:39.720 --> 00:00:41.510
These are all people who have never seen

00:00:41.510 --> 00:00:44.010
or touched the product.

00:00:44.010 --> 00:00:47.540
They probably see the bold claim.

00:00:47.540 --> 00:00:50.460
Now, anytime somebody makes a bold claim,

00:00:50.460 --> 00:00:51.600
it's going to be questioned.

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:55.210
Now, we can back up that
bold claim with science,

00:00:55.210 --> 00:00:58.200
but when the readers of the science,

00:00:58.200 --> 00:00:59.710
which might be the readers

00:00:59.710 --> 00:01:01.940
on this particular bodybuilding website

00:01:03.290 --> 00:01:04.640
that has a forum section,

00:01:04.640 --> 00:01:06.290
and this is where it's discussed,

00:01:07.430 --> 00:01:11.220
they probably can't read
scientific literature.

00:01:11.220 --> 00:01:15.430
And, in their defense,
it's not easy reading.

00:01:15.430 --> 00:01:19.068
So they may be very confused,

00:01:19.068 --> 00:01:20.910
that's part of the reason

00:01:20.910 --> 00:01:23.890
why we're working with so many athletes.

00:01:23.890 --> 00:01:28.890
And you can see tons of
athletes on the website.

00:01:29.330 --> 00:01:31.880
There's a whole wall of pro athletes

00:01:31.880 --> 00:01:34.830
that have switched over
to X3 over weights,

00:01:34.830 --> 00:01:36.590
'cause remember a performance athlete

00:01:36.590 --> 00:01:38.670
doesn't really care about what they lift.

00:01:38.670 --> 00:01:40.990
They care about what they do on the field,

00:01:40.990 --> 00:01:42.940
and that matters a lot more.

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:45.550
So I think their priority is right,

00:01:45.550 --> 00:01:48.030
and they're, of course,
highly muscular people.

00:01:48.030 --> 00:01:49.620
They put on a lotta size

00:01:49.620 --> 00:01:54.030
and gain a lotta strength
and speed with X3.

00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:57.060
So (clears throat) back
to the negative reviews.

00:01:57.060 --> 00:01:59.180
There's a couple of different groups

00:01:59.180 --> 00:02:01.573
that are pushing out negative reviews.

00:02:02.650 --> 00:02:05.410
The most comical one is the gym owners.

00:02:05.410 --> 00:02:09.150
Well, obviously, we have
tens of thousands of people

00:02:09.150 --> 00:02:11.402
who have bought X3, love X3,

00:02:11.402 --> 00:02:13.530
and use it all the time

00:02:13.530 --> 00:02:14.910
and they quit their gym membership

00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:16.870
and they're bragging about
how much money they save

00:02:16.870 --> 00:02:20.170
by quitting the gym and getting an X3.

00:02:20.170 --> 00:02:24.380
Yeah, I mean, they're not
gonna be happy with me

00:02:24.380 --> 00:02:25.440
or with the product,

00:02:25.440 --> 00:02:28.810
and so some of 'em are
out there making videos

00:02:28.810 --> 00:02:31.923
that are full of all
kinds of dishonest stuff,

00:02:33.590 --> 00:02:35.630
lying about me, lying about the company,

00:02:35.630 --> 00:02:37.860
and trying to discredit the product.

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:40.530
I actually really like
it when they pick on me

00:02:40.530 --> 00:02:44.300
because they know they
can't say enough negative

00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:47.280
that's accurate about the product,

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:48.830
because they have to lie to do that,

00:02:48.830 --> 00:02:51.440
so then they make up stuff about me,

00:02:51.440 --> 00:02:52.683
which is,

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:56.600
it's a personal attack

00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:58.680
because they can't discredit the product,

00:02:58.680 --> 00:03:01.670
which is hilarious,
'cause what do I matter?

00:03:01.670 --> 00:03:02.680
I don't matter at all.

00:03:02.680 --> 00:03:04.440
I mean, does the product work or not?

00:03:04.440 --> 00:03:07.220
So you can tell by looking at the website

00:03:07.220 --> 00:03:08.420
and the before and after pictures,

00:03:08.420 --> 00:03:10.410
by looking at the users forum

00:03:10.410 --> 00:03:15.060
and seeing tens of thousands
of people using the product

00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:16.100
and succeeding with it,

00:03:16.100 --> 00:03:19.580
putting on, as I say frequently,

00:03:19.580 --> 00:03:21.560
20 pounds of muscle in six months.

00:03:21.560 --> 00:03:23.747
You won't do that with anything else.

00:03:23.747 --> 00:03:28.320
So I find those comical,
so there's gym owners.

00:03:28.320 --> 00:03:30.490
Now there's some personal trainers

00:03:30.490 --> 00:03:32.950
who get upset by X3

00:03:32.950 --> 00:03:35.130
because some of them have come up with

00:03:35.130 --> 00:03:38.700
sorta like a weird, convoluted program

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:40.780
involving all of the equipment in the gym

00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:46.523
so that you really need the
gym to do their program.

00:03:49.678 --> 00:03:52.030
That's unfortunate, these
people aren't too bright,

00:03:52.030 --> 00:03:55.720
because the smarter
personal trainers get X3

00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:57.920
and train people with X3,

00:03:57.920 --> 00:03:59.393
either in the park,

00:04:00.860 --> 00:04:05.670
or at their home or at
their clients' homes.

00:04:05.670 --> 00:04:08.710
So what I say to personal trainers is

00:04:08.710 --> 00:04:11.530
why allow the club to make the money

00:04:11.530 --> 00:04:13.850
when you could make it all?

00:04:13.850 --> 00:04:16.740
So go and take X3 to somebody

00:04:16.740 --> 00:04:19.750
and put 'em through the
greatest workout of their life,

00:04:19.750 --> 00:04:21.540
which it will be, by the way,

00:04:21.540 --> 00:04:23.811
and they'll know it immediately.

00:04:23.811 --> 00:04:26.810
So that's really,

00:04:26.810 --> 00:04:28.740
I think it's just the
confused personal trainers

00:04:28.740 --> 00:04:31.050
that don't really fully get that yet.

00:04:31.050 --> 00:04:36.050
Now we also get some
negative videos and reviews

00:04:36.300 --> 00:04:39.250
from people who manufacture
fitness equipment.

00:04:39.250 --> 00:04:40.470
Of course, we get a negative review,

00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:42.340
it doesn't really make sense.

00:04:42.340 --> 00:04:44.850
And so we look into who the person is,

00:04:44.850 --> 00:04:46.770
and it turns out, like this (laughs),

00:04:46.770 --> 00:04:48.480
couple of reviews we've got

00:04:48.480 --> 00:04:52.110
were from home fitness
equipment manufacturers.

00:04:52.110 --> 00:04:56.400
We just traced it back
to the source, and yeah,

00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:58.340
X3 is $550

00:04:58.340 --> 00:05:02.770
and if you sell a plate-loaded

00:05:02.770 --> 00:05:05.680
multi-station device,

00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:09.840
that's gonna be like a $2,000 price point.

00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:13.500
And so we can do with
X3 better, much better,

00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:16.960
than one of these home gym-type things.

00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:18.620
Plus also, when you have one of those,

00:05:18.620 --> 00:05:21.920
you lose a room of your house,

00:05:21.920 --> 00:05:25.890
whereas X3, even with all the
banding and the ground plate,

00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:27.520
fits in a drawer,

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:30.130
or you can put it in
the travel carrying case

00:05:30.130 --> 00:05:31.520
and you can slide it under your bed

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:32.780
or something like that.

00:05:32.780 --> 00:05:35.480
So you don't need to lose
a room in your house.

00:05:35.480 --> 00:05:37.390
It's better, so, you know,

00:05:37.390 --> 00:05:39.120
they see this and they're very upset,

00:05:39.120 --> 00:05:41.550
and some of 'em probably lose customers

00:05:41.550 --> 00:05:44.330
who end up going with X3
and succeeding with it.

00:05:44.330 --> 00:05:47.100
So a lotta conflicts of interest

00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:48.513
in those negative reviews.

00:05:49.440 --> 00:05:51.660
And then, there's always the customer

00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:53.940
that didn't really
understand what they bought,

00:05:53.940 --> 00:05:56.310
and they might say,

00:05:56.310 --> 00:05:57.740
I remember we got a one-star review

00:05:57.740 --> 00:06:01.790
from somebody who said,
"Bicep curls are so 1990s."

00:06:01.790 --> 00:06:06.120
And I thought, like, okay,
so don't do 'em (laughs).

00:06:06.120 --> 00:06:10.510
But the guy was a jerk
and gave us a one-star.

00:06:10.510 --> 00:06:14.170
So, okay, well, there's
those guys out there, too.

00:06:14.170 --> 00:06:18.520
But over time, we are
getting so many people

00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:21.370
that are so happy with the product,

00:06:21.370 --> 00:06:25.050
it'll drown out all the
clowns and confusion

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:26.490
and people who have never touched it

00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:28.260
and think they know everything,

00:06:28.260 --> 00:06:30.490
which, by the way, in
case you haven't noticed,

00:06:30.490 --> 00:06:34.340
the internet is full of people
who know absolutely nothing

00:06:34.340 --> 00:06:38.673
yet present themselves as
experts on many subjects.

